The paper deals with the problem of hierarchical clustering, which is a fundamental problem in computer science and falls under the category of data structures (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses approximation algorithms based on sparsest cut and spreading metrics, which are topics in information theory (cs.IT) and signal processing (cs.SI). Finally, the paper mentions inapproximability results, which are often studied in the context of computational complexity (cs.CC).
